description._content: Catalog #: 09_01585 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Hankow, China Additional Information: Elwyn Gibbon (on right) and George H. Weigle at Hankow, 1938. Weigle is wearing the Chinese airmen's identification silk flag supposedly to keep the Chinese from murdering the ""foreign devils"" in case of shot down or forced landing. Weigle allegedly served in Spain prior to his China adventure. Killed In Action over Chungking 5/4/38, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Tags: Elwyn H.
